---
By: Plutarch
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 87
    Verse: 1
Tags:
  - Death
---
Not by lamentations and mournful chants ought we to celebrate the
funeral of a good man, but by hymns, for in ceasing to be numbered to
mortals, he enters upon the heritage of a diviner life.
